# Web Search Tools Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and configure your API keys

# =============================================================================
# Web Search Engine API Keys
# =============================================================================

# Google Search via SerpAPI (Required for Google search, news, flights, events)
# Sign up at: https://serpapi.com/dashboard
# Get your API key from the dashboard
# SERPAPI_API_KEY=your_serpapi_key_here

# Tavily Research API (Required for advanced research searches)
# Sign up at: https://tavily.com/
# Get your API key from the dashboard
# TAVILI_API_KEY=your_tavily_key_here

# NewsAPI (Required for news-specific searches)
# Sign up at: https://newsapi.org/
# Get your API key from the dashboard
# NEWSAPI_API_KEY=your_newsapi_key_here

# =============================================================================
# Engine Configuration Notes
# =============================================================================

# The following engines do NOT require API keys:
# - DuckDuckGo (duckduckgo) - Free web search
# - Wikipedia (wikipedia) - Free educational content
# - Hacker News (hackernews) - Free tech community content

# The following engines require API keys:
# - Google SERP (google_serp) - Requires SERPAPI_API_KEY
# - Tavily (tavily) - Requires TAVILI_API_KEY  
# - NewsAPI (newsapi) - Requires NEWSAPI_API_KEY

# =============================================================================
# Usage Examples
# =============================================================================

# With no API keys configured, you can still use:
# - DuckDuckGo for general web search
# - Wikipedia for educational content
# - Hacker News for tech community content

# With API keys configured, you get access to:
# - Google Search results (more comprehensive)
# - Google News (better news coverage)
# - Google Flights (flight search)
# - Google Events (event search)
# - Tavily Research (advanced research with content extraction)
# - NewsAPI (comprehensive news from multiple sources)

